Ticket 4 — Printer Not Responding
User: David P.
Department: Sales
Issue: “Printer says offline even though it’s plugged in.”

🔍 Technician Notes
Common issue: spooler crash, driver issue, or network printer offline

User attempted to reinstall printer with no success

🧪 Troubleshooting Steps
Followed Printer Troubleshooting Workflow

Verified Print Spooler Service

Cleared print queue

Checked printer IP and pinged device

Reinstalled printer using correct TCP/IP port

🖨️ Findings
Print Spooler service was stuck in “Stopping” state.

✅ Resolution
Force‑restarted spooler:

Code
Stop-Service spooler -Force
Start-Service spooler
Printer immediately came online.

📌 Preventative Recommendation
Update printer driver package across department.
